cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use ResearchQ in your research, please cite it using this metadata."
title: "ResearchQ: AI-powered, self-hosted systematic literature review platform"
abstract: >-
  ResearchQ is an open-source, self-hosted platform for conducting
  systematic literature reviews. It combines the OpenAlex academic graph
  with large-language-model assistance for relevance screening and
  metadata extraction, and ships with eighteen peer-reviewed review
  methodologies (PRISMA, Cochrane, Kitchenham, JBI, GRADE, and others).
  The tool runs locally using SQLite and Node.js, keeping all paper
  data, prompts, and extractions on the researcher's own machine.
